overview: The user initiated a project to enhance their Sleep Questionnaire
  Application by integrating a database for response storage, developing an
  admin dashboard for data access, and implementing an authentication system.
  After an initial codebase evaluation, the agent outlined a plan covering
  database schema creation, API route development, and UI for the dashboard. A
  key decision point involved simplifying the authentication mechanism;
  initially, a custom session management was proposed, but upon user inquiry, it
  was streamlined to leverage Next.js middleware for more efficient route
  protection and a basic cookie-based session. The agent successfully
  implemented all planned features, including updating demographic fields,
  creating Prisma models, developing API endpoints for data submission and
  retrieval (including CSV export), and building the admin login and dashboard
  pages. The database setup was guided, and the entire functionality was
  verified through browser-based testing, confirming that questionnaire
  responses were saved and accessible via the authenticated admin dashboard.
